findings.title: Safe math
findings.description: Using Solidity version lower than 0.8.0 can cause code blocks without safe math to fail if inappropriate values are used.

findings.title: swapBack function distributes reflection and marketing fee and adds liquidity
findings.description: The swapBack function is responsible for distributing reflection and marketing fees as well as adding liquidity.

findings.title: Liquidity Fee Misdirection
findings.description: If dynamic liquidity fee will equal to zero, liquidity fee part goes to marketing.

findings.title: Unaudited Interface Functions
findings.description: The reflector(Cashier) interface is provided without implementation, so its functions are not audited.
